{{> menu user=user active=active}}

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="columns is-vcentered">
      <div class="column">
        <h1 class="title is-3">About WeatherTop</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          A weather-station web app extended with an IoT pipeline (MQTT + edge device simulation + cloud storage).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="column is-narrow">
        <a class="button is-primary" href="https://github.com/edabelt/WeatherTop" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="columns is-multiline">

      <!-- Base WeatherTop -->
      <div class="column is-12-tablet is-6-desktop">
        <div class="box">
          <h2 class="title is-5">Core Features (WeatherTop)</h2>
          <ul class="content">
            <li>Add stations by city name or coordinates</li>
            <li>View live conditions from OpenWeather</li>
            <li>Save manual reports and see temperature trends</li>
            <li>Station overview with map and forecast</li>
            <li>Delete stations with cascading report removal</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- IoT Extension -->
      <div class="column is-12-tablet is-6-desktop">
        <div class="box">
          <h2 class="title is-5">IoT Extension (WeatherTop-IoT)</h2>
          <ul class="content">
            <li>Simulated edge node (Python) generates telemetry every few seconds</li>
            <li>MQTT publish/subscribe messaging via a public Mosquitto broker</li>
            <li>Discrete events (e.g. <code>TEMP_HIGH</code>) generated on threshold breach</li>
            <li>Backend subscribes to MQTT topics and maintains live IoT state</li>
            <li>Telemetry & events persisted locally to CSV for history and analytics</li>
            <li>IoT dashboard at <code>/iot-view</code> showing live + recent data</li>
            <li>Cloud integration: telemetry forwarded to ThingSpeak for charts</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Networking / Rubric -->
      <div class="column is-12-tablet is-6-desktop">
        <div class="box">
          <h2 class="title is-5">Networking Concepts Demonstrated</h2>
          <ul class="content">
            <li>Application layer: MQTT (real-time messaging) and HTTP (cloud APIs)</li>
            <li>Transport layer: TCP (MQTT and HTTP run over TCP)</li>
            <li>Network layer: IP addressing and routing</li>
            <li>Link layer: switching and ARP resolution</li>
            <li>Encapsulation across layers and event-driven architecture</li>
            <li>Packet Tracer simulation of a LAN with switch + router + end hosts</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="is-size-7 has-text-grey">
            Supporting documentation: <code>docs/network/architecture.md</code>,
            <code>docs/network/networking-notes.md</code>, <code>docs/network/packet-tracer.md</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stack -->
      <div class="column is-12-tablet is-6-desktop">
        <div class="box">
          <h2 class="title is-5">Stack</h2>
          <ul class="content">
            <li>Node.js, Express, Express-Handlebars, Bulma</li>
            <li>Leaflet maps, custom SVG charts</li>
            <li>LowDB (JSON storage)</li>
            <li>MQTT client (Node) + paho-mqtt (Python)</li>
            <li>CSV persistence for IoT history</li>
            <li>ThingSpeak (cloud dashboards & visualisation)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Data & Credits -->
      <div class="column is-12">
        <div class="box">
          <h2 class="title is-5">Data & Credits</h2>
          <p class="content">
            Live weather and geocoding by OpenWeather. Maps Â© OpenStreetMap contributors, rendered with Leaflet.
            IoT telemetry is generated by a simulated edge node and transported via MQTT. Cloud charts are provided
            via ThingSpeak.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="has-text-centered">
      {{#if user}}
        <a class="button is-primary" href="/dashboard">Go to your Dashboard</a>
        <a class="button is-link is-light" href="/iot-view" style="margin-left: .5rem;">Open IoT Dashboard</a>
      {{else}}
        <a class="button is-primary" href="/login">Log in</a>
        <a class="button is-light" href="/signup">Sign up</a>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

